          <text>B12-dependent clone</text>
        </annotation>
        <annotation id="T10">
          <infon key="brat-id">T10</infon>
          <infon key="type">Change</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="9" offset="1077"/>
          <text>evolution</text>
        </annotation>
        <relation id="E5">
          <infon key="brat-id">E5</infon>
          <infon key="type">Change</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">event</infon>
          <node refid="T10" role="Change"/>
          <node refid="T9" role="Theme"/>
        </relation>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">7</infon>
        <offset>1149</offset>
        <text>Genetic characterization of this line reveals a type-II Gulliver-related transposable element integrated into the B12-independent methionine synthase gene (METE), knocking out gene function and fundamentally altering the physiology of the alga.
</text>
